Character Array /ArrayList
1-char [] arr= ['g','e','e','k','s']
2-String class:
String class is not immutable
String str="geeks"
or
String str=new String("geeks");

3-StringBuffer Class:
Description--:
It is thread safe class and used in multithreaded environement
StringBuffer str=new StringBuffer("geeks");
4-StringBuilder Class:
Description--:
It used only within a thread .when you create a threat safe class that involves extra over head as well that extra overheads is not in StringBuilder
StringBuilder str=new StringBuilder ("geeks");

String Class:

Example :
Class Test{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        String str="geeks";
        System.out.println(str.length);
        System.out.println(str.charAt(3);
        System.out.println(str.substring(2);
        System.out.println(str.substring(2,5);
}
}
Ouput is:
5
k
eks
ek

Example-2
Class Test{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        String s1="geeks";
        String s2="geeks";
        if(s1==s2)
        System.out.println("Yes");
        else
        System.out.println("No");
        String s3=new String("geeks");
        if(s1==s3)
        System.out.println("Yes");
        else
        System.out.println("No");
    }
}